    <chapter id="batchrep-developer-debugging">
        <title>Debugging</title>
        <indexterm type="batch"><primary>logging</primary></indexterm>
        <para>Log output from Batch Replicator is a useful tool for debugging issues. Because Batch Replicator is built
      on top of Java WS Core, developer debugging is the same as described in <olink
      targetdoc="javawscoreDeveloper" targetptr="javawscore-developer-debugging"/>. You can also find information about 
        sys admin logging in <olink
            targetdoc="batchrepAdmin" targetptr="batchrep-admin-debugging"/>.</para>
        
        <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
      href="../../../../common/javawscore/Java_WS_Core_Logging_Frag.xml"
      xpointer="javawscore-developer-logging-general"/>
              
      
        <section><title>Enable Debug Logging for Batch Replicator</title>
        <para>To turn on debug logging for Batch Replicator, add the line:
        <screen> log4j.category.org.globus.replica=DEBUG</screen>
        to the appropriate properties file.</para>
        </section>
